title: First Sergeant (Associate Operations Manager)
description: Directed day-to-day staff operations for a team of over 110 employees, supervised and managed the installation, operation, and maintenance of systems within select Information Mission Areas. Oversaw signal support functions within integrated Department of Defense telecommunications networks, to include coordinating the resolution of communication difficulties between United States, North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) forces and other Foreign Allied military networks as well as the inclusion of commercial telecommunications activities. Developed and enforced unit level communication maintenance programs, policies, and procedures. Planned and coordinated logistical support activities for employees conducting network operations. Provided advice and technical assistance to senior policy makers, which allowed critical decisions to be made. Tracked all operational reports for the organization, maintained accountability of the personnel assigned to each department and managed all human resource management within the organization.

title: Senior Communications Maintenance and C4I Manager
description: Held multifaceted responsibility for deep maintenance of multiple levels of an organizational telecommunications system and the implementation of Command, Control, Communications, Computers and Intelligence (C4I) practices and equipment throughout several levels of digital data networks, including radio, switching, cable, and automation in an austere environments. Supervised the installation, operation, strapping, re-strapping, preventive maintenance checks and services (PMCS) and unit level maintenance on all communication security (COMSEC) encryption devices. Monitored all network traffic and directed the restoration and alternate routing of circuits, trunks, links, and systems in the event of an outage or system failure. Developed and implemented lower level communication equipment maintenance programs that improved productivity. Provided maintenance advice and technical assistance to subordinates as well as decisive information to senior management. Developed frequency operational requirements, telecommunications service requests, and disseminated operational information to ensure command and control communication connectivity. Requested and ensured the appropriate logistical support was available at all times to perform routine and complex maintenance task. Assimilated system/network statistic reporting while developing training programs for employees developed from the data analysis.

title: US ARMY Enterprise Network Engineer/ Maintainer
company: XVIII Airborne Corps G6/ 50th Signal BN
description: Directly responsible for maintaining US Army Enterprise Network infrastructure to include specialized architectures within the entire XVIII Airborne Corps secure Network. Supported many subordinate entities with communication network analysis and monitoring through the use of Simple Network Management protocol (SNMP) software applications. Performed level 2 Triage for circuit outages and link restorations along with the management of Network Operation Security Center. Supervised and a managed a Small Extension Nodal section for a forward deployed US Army signal organization. The Section consisted of five switching shelters designed to conduct switching, multiplexing, and communications security (COMSEC) operations for secure digital voice and data communications across a large spectrum.
